Solar Blade.description: Requires a turn to charge before attacking.

Speed Swap.description: Exchanges the user's Speed with the target's.

Nightmare.description: Target loses 1/4 its max HP every turn as long as it's asleep.

Gravity.description: Disables moves and immunities that involve flying or levitating for five turns.

Shadow Blitz.description: Inflicts regular damage with no additional effect.

Meditate.description: Raises the user's Attack by one stage.

Drain Punch.description: Drains half the damage inflicted to heal the user.

Discharge.description: Has a chance to paralyze the target.

Last Resort.description: Can only be used after all of the user's other moves have been used.

Leech Life.description: Drains half the damage inflicted to heal the user.

Protect.description: Prevents any moves from hitting the user this turn.

Spikes.description: Scatters Spikes, hurting opposing Pokemon that switch in.

Thunder Shock.description: Has a chance to paralyze the target.

Retaliate.description: Has double power if a friendly Pokemon fainted last turn.

Belly Drum.description: User pays half its max HP to max out its Attack.

Block.description: Prevents the target from leaving battle.

Sketch.description: Permanently becomes the target's last used move.

Psycho Shift.description: Transfers the user's major status effect to the target.

Defense Curl.description: Raises user's Defense by one stage.

Shadow Sneak.description: Inflicts regular damage with no additional effect.

Natural Gift.description: Power and type depend on the held berry.

Shadow Wave.description: Inflicts regular damage with no additional effect.

Rock Slide.description: Has a chance to make the target flinch.

Meteor Mash.description: Has a chance to raise the user's Attack by one stage.

Megahorn.description: Inflicts regular damage with no additional effect.

Swords Dance.description: Raises the user's Attack by two stages.

U-turn.description: User must switch out after attacking.

Guardian of Alola.description: Damages the target for 75% of its remaining HP.

Shadow Half.description: Halves HP of all Pokemon on the field.  Must recharge

Subzero Slammer.description: Inflicts regular damage with no additional effect.

Signal Beam.description: Has a chance to confuse the target.

Rock Throw.description: Inflicts regular damage with no additional effect.

Shadow Bolt.description: Has a chance to paralyze the target.

Echoed Voice.description: Power increases by 100% for each consecutive use by any friendly Pokemon, to a maximum of 200.

Hidden Power.description: Power and type depend upon user's IVs.  Power can range from 30 to 70.

10,000,000 Volt Thunderbolt.description: Inflicts regular damage with no additional effect.

Strength Sap.description: Heals the user by the target's current Attack stat and lowers the target's Attack by one stage.

Grass Pledge.description: With Fire Pledge, damages opposing Pokemon for 1/8 their max HP every turn for four turns.

Laser Focus.description: Guarantees a critical hit with the user's next move.

Outrage.description: Hits every turn for 2-3 turns, then confuses the user.

First Impression.description: Can only be used as the first move after the user enters battle.

Whirlpool.description: Prevents the target from leaving battle and inflicts 1/16 its max HP in damage for 2-5 turns.

Venom Drench.description: Lowers the target's Attack, Special Attack, and Speed by one stage if it is poisoned.

Land's Wrath.description: Inflicts regular damage with no additional effect.

Power Trip.description: Power is higher the more the user's stats have been raised, to a maximum of 31 times.

Taunt.description: For the next few turns, the target can only use damaging moves.

Dive.description: User dives underwater, dodging all attacks, and hits next turn.

Rage Powder.description: Redirects the target's single-target effects to the user for this turn.

Payback.description: Power is doubled if the target has already moved this turn.

Telekinesis.description: Moves have 100% accuracy against the target for three turns.

Lock-On.description: Ensures that the user's next move will hit the target.

Safeguard.description: Protects the user's field from major status ailments and confusion for five turns.

Judgment.description: If the user is holding a appropriate plate or drive, the damage inflicted will match it.

Clanging Scales.description: Lowers the user's Defense by one stage after inflicting damage.

Parting Shot.description: Lowers all targets' Attack and Special Attack by one stage.  Makes the user switch out.

Roar.description: Immediately ends wild battles.  Forces trainers to switch Pokemon.

Bind.description: Prevents the target from fleeing and inflicts damage for 2-5 turns.

Headbutt.description: Has a chance to make the target flinch.

Extreme Evoboost.description: Raises all of the user's stats by two stages.

Mirror Coat.description: Inflicts twice the damage the user received from the last special hit it took.

Pound.description: Inflicts regular damage with no additional effect.

Steel Wing.description: Has a chance to raise the user's Defense by one stage.

Seed Bomb.description: Inflicts regular damage with no additional effect.

Black Hole Eclipse.description: Inflicts regular damage with no additional effect.

Superpower.description: Lowers the user's Attack and Defense by one stage after inflicting damage.

Miracle Eye.description: Forces the target to have no evasion, and allows it to be hit by Psychic moves even if it's Dark.

Spider Web.description: Prevents the target from leaving battle.

Ingrain.description: Prevents the user from leaving battle.  User regains 1/16 of its max HP every turn.

Psychic.description: Has a chance to lower the target's Special Defense by one stage.

Silver Wind.description: Has a chance to raise all of the user's stats by one stage.

Tickle.description: Lowers the target's Attack and Defense by one stage.

Wild Charge.description: User receives 1/4 the damage it inflicts in recoil.

Light Screen.description: Reduces damage from special attacks by 50% for five turns.

Astonish.description: Has a chance to make the target flinch.

Healing Wish.description: User faints.  Its replacement has its HP fully restored and any major status effect removed.

Dragon Breath.description: Has a chance to paralyze the target.

Fleur Cannon.description: Lowers the user's Special Attack by two stages after inflicting damage.

Baby-Doll Eyes.description: Lowers the target's Attack by one stage.

Aeroblast.description: Has an increased chance for a critical hit.

Thousand Arrows.description: Grounds the target, and hits even Flying-type or levitating Pokemon.

Ice Beam.description: Has a chance to freeze the target.

Confusion.description: Has a chance to confuse the target.

Pursuit.description: Has double power against, and can hit, Pokemon attempting to switch out.

Mach Punch.description: Inflicts regular damage with no additional effect.

Rage.description: If the user is hit after using this move, its Attack rises by one stage.

Wish.description: User will recover half its max HP at the end of the next turn.

Defog.description: Lowers the target's evasion by one stage.  Removes field effects from the enemy field.

Screech.description: Lowers the target's Defense by two stages.

Simple Beam.description: Changes the target's ability to Simple.

Force Palm.description: Has a chance to paralyze the target.

Mimic.description: Copies the target's last used move.

Hyper Beam.description: User foregoes its next turn to recharge.

Volt Switch.description: User must switch out after attacking.

Focus Punch.description: If the user takes damage before attacking, the attack is canceled.

Encore.description: Forces the target to repeat its last used move every turn for 2 to 6 turns.

Origin Pulse.description: Inflicts regular damage with no additional effect.

Bubble Beam.description: Has a chance to lower the target's Speed by one stage.

Savage Spin-Out.description: Inflicts regular damage with no additional effect.

Scratch.description: Inflicts regular damage with no additional effect.

Mega Drain.description: Drains half the damage inflicted to heal the user.

Vacuum Wave.description: Inflicts regular damage with no additional effect.

Geomancy.description: Takes one turn to charge, then raises the user's Special Attack, Special Defense, and Speed by two stages.

Slack Off.description: Heals the user by half its max HP.

Fairy Wind.description: Inflicts regular damage with no additional effect.

Growth.description: Raises the user's Attack and Special Attack by one stage.

Sludge Wave.description: Has a chance to poison the target.

Electro Ball.description: Power is higher when the user has greater Speed than the target, up to a maximum of 150.

Head Charge.description: User receives 1/4 the damage it inflicts in recoil.

Acid.description: Has a chance to lower the target's Special Defense by one stage.
